## Widget

- Before material changes, call `visualise_read_me` from `jaztools`; use the closest module (`chart`/`data_viz` for metrics, `mockup` for status/UI, `diagram` for flows).
{{- if .FilePath}}
- Widget file: {{.FilePath}} — create or overwrite it this run, then publish it.
{{- end}}
- Write one self-contained HTML fragment under 1 MB: no <!doctype>, <html>, <head>, or <body>; use shell if file tools refuse the path.
- Tile quality floor: one stable root, scoped CSS, clear hierarchy, deliberate spacing, finished styling; no fixed positioning, viewport units, clipped overflow, placeholder text, dead space, forms, or action buttons.
- For news/status/tracker tiles, surface the strongest 2-4 signals first with compact rows, chips, or metrics. Use one internal scroll region only when genuinely needed.
- Publish with `visualise_publish_widget` and fix validation errors in the same run.
